reviewText: First off, let me say that I am thoroughly enjoying Ultimate Spider-Man. That being said however, for fans who want to complete the series, in order, I have to vent. Disney and whoever is marketing this series is making the level of frustration on this almost unbearable, thus the 2 star rating. Sure I know Jeph Loeb wanted to kill all the previous Marvel Animated series because they had story arcs that were "too involved" but I think our kids are smarter than that. From as young as I can remember (age 4) and I am 37 now, my favorite animated series have always been the ones that have long meaningful story arcs, not the ones that were all stand-alone and never went anywhere. However, the strategy seems to have worked somewhat.  Twelve of the 26 first season episodes are on this two disc set. They tried to pick the "Avengers-centric" ones no doubt to capitalize on last year's movie. Does that mean they have little faith in the remaining 14 episodes? And what  about season Two just getting started? PLEASE READ THIS DISNEY.... Fans would REALLY REALLY like their episodes in chronological order.  I hope you can learn from this and release season 2 in that manner and all future Marvel related DVD's.Someone else posted the episode names; here is the number sequence...Disc One:1, 2, 3, 10, 15, 21Disc Two: 5, 7, 9, 19, 20, 23You can get the whole series on Amazon instant Video or Netflix. At least they are in order; this may be the best way to go.

reviewText: I am a seasoned Marvel fan and while many people bash this show because it's not mature or the same as other spidey cartoons...I appreciate what they are doing. You have to get it. If you GET spider-man then you know he is a comedian at heart and a trickster. Spidey in the comics has always cracked jokes and this show finally goes one step beyond just letting you hear his witty thoughts it lets you SEE his insane thoughts! This is EXACTLY what would be going through a 16 yr old Peter Parker's head. The breaking of the fourth wall is something I like about this series because spider-man is always talking to himself anyway in every other cartoon and comic. You have to appreciate the breaking of the fourth wall represents him having a conversation with himself. Similarly he is having a self confliction when he see's his good side and bad side float around him like little angel & devil spidey. For long time fans of the comics they have plenty of cameos of characters you don't normally see in a cartoon. There is a lot of easter egg stuff that goes into these episodes including many apperences by Stan Lee himself in like every episode. This show is fun, hip, and funny. It's a great modern take on the spidey and his amazing friends thing while trying to incorporate new themes such as SHEILD from the avengers movie and cartoon and high school. There are a lot of changes but hey it's BETTER then you'd expect from disney or is it exactly? idk but If I can like it so can you. I have a custom made spider-man suit I design and my mom sewed together at age 23! I am a big fan of spidey and trust me i'm critical when it comes to his stuff. I HATE SPECTACULAR SPIDER-MAN cartoon and that blasted cgi MTV version those shows suck! If anyone tells you Spectacular spider-man is better than this show they are smoking banana peels. As an artist even I can appriciate the animation being crisp and fluid in this series and not crappy like in spectacular spidey (you want childish? put on spectacular spider-man series it looks like its drawn for 2-3 yr olds)
summary: Im 33 yrs old and I LOVE this show. Nuff Said!

reviewText: Disney/marvel are really pissing me off lately. They cancelled spectacular spider-man just to make this piece of crap and that was a really good show. They are doing the same thing with avengers earth's mightiest heroes. That show, also amazing, was cancelled and replaced with avengers assemble- basically a disney-fied, dumbed down new cartoon to capitalize on the success of the avengers movie. And marvel STILL has not released the 1990s animated spider-man series, my favorite and arguably the best interpretation of the character outside of comics. They released the x-men series so why not spider-man? I don't understand what is going on up there at marvel/disney other than a bunch of greedy morons who have lost their creativity or at least stopped caring about the quality of their product. It seems like they care more about merchandising opportunities than the quality of the actual stories. And just to be clear- I did not buy this dvd. I just hate this show so much I felt compelled to write a review.
summary: This show is aimed at the very young and very dumb. And even they won't enjoy it.
